WEBVTT



00:00:00.768 --> 00:00:05.920
Well hello friends and thank you for joining me in our daily reading from God's holy word

00:00:05.760 --> 00:00:15.808
Today we're reading Mark chapter 9 just verses 1 to 13 today. In this lesson we come to the most amazing event in the life of

00:00:15.328 --> 00:00:19.104
The life of Jesus between his birth and his death.

00:00:18.976 --> 00:00:21.504
It's called his transfiguration.

00:00:21.600 --> 00:00:22.720
In it

00:00:22.592 --> 00:00:25.568
We see the unveiling of his glory,

00:00:25.472 --> 00:00:28.320
And catch a glimpse of his majesty.

00:00:28.640 --> 00:00:30.752
Before we read, let's pray.

00:00:31.040 --> 00:00:36.928
Our Father in heaven, give us eyes to see and ears to hear.

00:00:36.640 --> 00:00:39.520
And so do good to our souls.

00:00:39.584 --> 00:00:41.472
In Jesus name I pray.

00:00:41.664 --> 00:00:42.784
Amen.

00:00:43.392 --> 00:00:46.304
Mark chapter 9 verses 1 to 13.

00:00:46.272 --> 00:00:48.128
And he said to them,

00:00:47.936 --> 00:00:53.888
"'Truly, I say to you, there are some standing here who will not taste death.'

00:00:53.792 --> 00:00:57.696
until they see the kingdom of God after it has come.

00:00:57.472 --> 00:00:59.040
With power.

00:00:59.616 --> 00:01:04.960
And after six days, Jesus took with him Peter and James and John.

00:01:04.960 --> 00:01:08.224
And led them up a high mountain by themselves.

00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:11.712
And he was transfigured before them.

00:01:11.424 --> 00:01:17.984
And his clothes became radiant, intensely white, as no one on earth could bleach them.

00:01:18.368 --> 00:01:19.872
And there appeared

00:01:19.744 --> 00:01:22.624
To them, Elijah with Moses,

00:01:22.592 --> 00:01:24.800
And they were talking with Jesus.

00:01:24.928 --> 00:01:28.416
And Peter said to Jesus, "Rabbi,

00:01:28.512 --> 00:01:31.104
It is good that we are here.

00:01:30.976 --> 00:01:36.608
1. Let us make three tents, one for you and one for Moses and one for Elijah. 2.

00:01:36.544 --> 00:01:40.768
For he did not know what to say, for they were terrified.

00:01:41.024 --> 00:01:48.672
And a cloud overshadowed them, and a voice came out of the cloud. This is my beloved son.

00:01:48.544 --> 00:01:50.720
Listen to him

00:01:51.072 --> 00:01:52.352
And suddenly,

00:01:52.352 --> 00:01:53.696
Looking around

00:01:53.920 --> 00:01:57.760
They no longer saw anyone with them, but Jesus only.

00:01:58.272 --> 00:02:00.608
And as they were coming down the mountain,

00:02:00.224 --> 00:02:04.448
he charged them to tell no one what they had seen.

00:02:04.320 --> 00:02:07.392
Until the son of Man had risen from the dead.

00:02:07.456 --> 00:02:13.344
So they kept the matter to themselves, questioning what this rising from the dead might mean.

00:02:13.280 --> 00:02:17.376
And they asked him, Why do the scribes say that?

00:02:17.344 --> 00:02:20.224
First, Elijah must come.

00:02:20.224 --> 00:02:21.600
And he said to them,

00:02:21.408 --> 00:02:25.248
Elijah does come first to restore all things.

00:02:25.184 --> 00:02:31.360
And how is it written of the son of Man that he should suffer many things and be treated with contempt?

00:02:32.064 --> 00:02:37.280
But I tell you that Elijah has come, and they did to him whatever they pleased.

00:02:37.248 --> 00:02:39.360
As it is written of him.

00:02:40.608 --> 00:02:42.880
Amen this is God's word

00:02:43.360 --> 00:02:47.520
What can help us most in times of trouble?

00:02:48.096 --> 00:02:56.736
getting our eyes off of ourselves in our dark circumstances and onto someone who outshines everything and everyone.

00:02:56.768 --> 00:03:06.816
and here we see Jesus glowing like lightning. Now that skeptic might say people don't glow. Well don't you think Matthew, Mark, Luke and John need that?

00:03:06.336 --> 00:03:06.976
that.

00:03:06.784 --> 00:03:10.432
You think Peter, James, and John lied about it?

00:03:10.208 --> 00:03:16.192
James was killed by Herod just a few years later, Peter, after that. Why would they die for a lie?

00:03:16.320 --> 00:03:22.752
Now, Jesus here promised his disciples that they would see the kingdom of God come in power.

00:03:23.008 --> 00:03:30.208
And about a week later he takes them up on a mountain to give them a foretaste of the glory he will have when he comes again in power.

00:03:30.976 --> 00:03:33.824
What do we learn from this transfiguration?

00:03:34.784 --> 00:03:43.392
Let me highlight two things. First, they see Jesus in the fullness of his glory. His radiance is our hope.

00:03:43.584 --> 00:03:52.416
In the days of Moses on Mount Sinai, maybe you remember that God came down in a cloud and spoke, and everyone was afraid.

00:03:52.448 --> 00:03:57.696
Moses went up on the mountain and got to see God's glory, but not his face.

00:03:57.760 --> 00:04:00.608
And when he came down, his own face,

00:04:00.512 --> 00:04:03.616
was shining with the reflected glory of God.

00:04:03.936 --> 00:04:11.328
now here centuries later on top of a mountain there's a cloud and god's voice and moses is back.

00:04:11.456 --> 00:04:15.104
but where Moses reflected the glory of God.

00:04:14.912 --> 00:04:17.376
Like the moon reflects the sun,

00:04:17.216 --> 00:04:22.240
Jesus produces the glory of God. It comes from Him.

00:04:22.368 --> 00:04:32.416
Jesus doesn't merely point us to the glory of God like Elijah or Moses did, but Jesus is the glory of God in human form. He is the reigning God.

00:04:31.936 --> 00:04:39.616
a radiance of the glory of God in him the whole fullness of deity dwells bodily.

00:04:39.904 --> 00:04:41.536
Usually

00:04:41.312 --> 00:04:45.280
His glory was veiled when he was upon the earth. he.

00:04:44.928 --> 00:04:54.496
never ceased being divine but he veiled it under the cloak of humanity here the curtain is pulled back so to speak

00:04:54.336 --> 00:04:56.608
To see Jesus as he is.

00:04:56.352 --> 00:04:59.136
As the father sees his own son.

00:04:59.424 --> 00:05:01.344
In his glory,

00:05:01.376 --> 00:05:03.456
Is our destiny.

00:05:03.584 --> 00:05:05.568
For all who look to him,

00:05:05.664 --> 00:05:11.264
We all, with unveiled face, beholding the glory of the Lord Jesus,

00:05:11.200 --> 00:05:16.896
Are being transformed into the same image from one degree of glory to another?

00:05:17.120 --> 00:05:18.560
When christ

00:05:18.400 --> 00:05:23.552
Who is our life appears, we also will appear with him in glory.

00:05:23.680 --> 00:05:25.728
And we shall be like him.

00:05:25.632 --> 00:05:27.264
For we shall see him.

00:05:27.200 --> 00:05:28.992
As he really is.

00:05:30.144 --> 00:05:32.480
Now the second thing I want you to see

00:05:32.320 --> 00:05:36.448
is would you look at the love of the father for his son?

00:05:37.024 --> 00:05:42.784
The voice speaks, This is my son, my beloved, whom I love.

00:05:42.880 --> 00:05:48.480
with you I'm well pleased I delight you I approve of you God is satisfied with his son

00:05:48.672 --> 00:05:49.856
Are you?

00:05:50.208 --> 00:05:52.992
And the father says you should listen to him

00:05:53.440 --> 00:05:54.688
Do you?

00:05:55.232 --> 00:05:57.440
Peter was babbling on.

00:05:57.312 --> 00:06:00.576
About making tents because he was so afraid.

00:06:00.672 --> 00:06:10.720
But it made sense from his perspective. Tent is the word for Tabernacle, and in Exodus, Moses went up on the mountain and met with God in the cloud and was told to build a.

00:06:10.240 --> 00:06:11.872
Build a tabernacle.

00:06:12.128 --> 00:06:21.888
a place where heaven and earth would unite, where God and men would meet together. Peter wants to perpetuate that. And God says, "My son is that."

00:06:21.728 --> 00:06:27.616
He is where heaven and earth meet. He is where God and man have fellowship together.

00:06:27.648 --> 00:06:30.816
and you can have fellowship with God

00:06:30.656 --> 00:06:32.032
In him.

00:06:31.936 --> 00:06:33.728
Through faith in him,

00:06:33.792 --> 00:06:35.136
Through him,

00:06:34.976 --> 00:06:40.128
we have access by the Holy Spirit to God the Father.

00:06:40.608 --> 00:06:48.544
Let us, then, with confidence, draw near to the throne of grace, and use our access, and ask for help in days of trouble.

00:06:48.576 --> 00:06:52.608
That we may receive mercy and find grace to help from him.

00:06:52.960 --> 00:06:54.560
In time of need.

00:06:55.552 --> 00:06:56.640
let's pray.

00:06:57.728 --> 00:07:02.816
Father in heaven, thank you for the hope that we have in Jesus and the help that we get.

00:07:02.688 --> 00:07:04.128
through Jesus.

00:07:04.256 --> 00:07:06.880
Help us to trust in you in Jesus' name.

00:07:07.104 --> 00:07:08.288
Amen.

00:07:08.736 --> 00:07:12.800
Amen. Well, thank you for listening in, and I hope you'll join me next time.
